<p align="center"><h2><span id="title">Range Shift </span></h2><img id="icon" src="../icons/maxent.png" /></p>

<p><span id="section">Brief Description</span></p>

Calculates a potential range shift from a baseline raster to a prediction raster. In fact it is a simple reclassification of values, which are reclassified to 3 index values. 
<p></p>
1 = Niche Contraction
2 = No Change
3 = Niche Expansion
<p><span id="section">Parameters</span></p>
<ul>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input Raster Baseline grid: </span> A SDM</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input Raster Prediction grid: </span> A SDM</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input Number: </span> Equidistant distance from the median indicating lower and higher ends.</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span> Output Results: </span> Range Shift map is added to QGIS. Working on automatic coloring ;) </p>
	</li>	
</ul>

</ul></p>

